oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Carmichael Inn
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Exterior view of the Carmichael Inn. The Carmichael Inn was built in 1821 and was located behind the courthouse in Loudon. he two-story log building was originally owned by John Hudson Carmichael (1780-1840) and served as a residence, stagecoach stop and railroad inn.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
